<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<!--
  Entitlements for the RaioPDF app binary only. The Rust externalBin sidecars
  (raiopdf-engine-host and raiopdf-mcp) are explicitly re-signed without
  entitlements by scripts/sign-macos-app-binaries.mjs after Tauri bundles the
  app.

  Apple Events is deliberately limited to the app process, which invokes
  Microsoft Word. Do not add it to a sidecar: granting it to the main app
  preserves the smallest practical Automation permission boundary.

  WKWebView's JavaScript JIT runs in Apple's out-of-process
  com.apple.WebKit.WebContent XPC service, which carries its own system
  entitlements - the host app does not need allow-jit. The Rust sidecars are
  plain native binaries with no JIT, no plugin loading, and no library
  injection.

  Runtime entitlements for the bundled payload interpreters live next to this
  file: jvm.entitlements (Temurin JRE) and node.entitlements (MCP Node
  runtime). Grant new entitlements here only with a proven necessity,
  documented in a comment.
-->
<dict>
	<key>com.apple.security.automation.apple-events</key>
	<true/>
</dict>
</plist>
